                <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
                    <li class="active"><a data-toggle="tab" href="control-database#tab-script">Script</a></li>
                    <li><a data-toggle="tab" href="control-database#tab-comment">
                        <i class="fa fa-comment-o"></i>
                                                    
                                                                                                (2)
                                                                                        Conversation
                                            </a></li>
                </ul>

                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/behat/edit/behat3/knpu/control-database.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Eventually, you'll need to insert test data at the beginning of your
scenarios. And that's when things get tricky. So, let's learn to do
this right.</p>
<p>First: never assume that there is data in the database at the beginning of a scenario.
Instead, you should put any data you need there intentionally with a <code>Given</code>. </p>
<p>Go to the top of this scenario and add:</p>
