<p>And that should do it!</p>
<p>We already have a user called <code>admin</code> in the database, so let's test this using <code>admin2</code>.
Give it a go!</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">./vendor/bin/behat features/web/authentication.feature</div></code></pre>
<p>This should not work, since this user isn't in the database yet... unless it's
created by the code we just wrote! Brilliant!</p>
<p>This is huge: we're guaranteeing there's an <code>admin2</code> user by bootstrapping our app
and being dangerous with all of our useful services.</p>

    
